snippet.textDisplay: Everyone is saying y’all only hate on Eminem bc he white, and that’s just pathetic. I mean I don’t like logic either but that’s just bc I don’t like their voice. That has nothing to do with their skin color. I liked “old” Eminem bc his shit was low key funny. That might sound dumb but I liked that about him. His fast shit is impressive but it’s not sth that makes me listen to him. When it hits it’s still like damn chill bro but it’s nothing that keeps me. I btw am not a hater, I just don’t agree with the whole Eminem is the 🐐 and all. As I said: I can listen to Em but it doesn’t reel me in like other rappers. I can listen to maybe one song at a time and to me it doesn’t give of a vibe. With Travis for example you got the whole psychedelic vibe and with Migos you get the I’m rich and I got your bitch vibe. Em does not radiate any feelings for me. It’s not really nostalgic or anything either, bc his themes have changed so much in the last 15 or so years. I know it might sound pathetic saying old em was better but I don’t see it as like and edgy quirky thing but it just is closer the me personally. I can connect with that way more than any of this new stuff.
